                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-20T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 20, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>772. Your 1221, July 13, 9 a.m. Department is informed that General Spalding left
                    Washington on July 14. The War Department is understood to have considerable
                    information in addition to that furnished by Lockard regarding denial activities
                    and plans respecting the oilfields under reference but the General was unable to
                    acquaint himself with them prior to departure.</p>
                <p>You and the Legation at Jidda are requested to facilitate General Spalding’s work
                    in every possible way.</p>
                <p>Local representative of Casoc has been informed and states that Dhahran will be
                    advised to expect this visit.</p>
                <p>Inform Jidda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
